## âœ… **Validation Checklist:**

Before importing, check your JSON has:
- [ ] Valid recipe name
- [ ] Cooking time as number (not string)
- [ ] Single emoji character
- [ ] At least 3 ingredients
- [ ] All categories match exactly
- [ ] At least 3 instruction steps
- [ ] Proper JSON formatting (no trailing commas)

## ğŸš¨ **Common Mistakes:**

âŒ **Wrong category names:**
```json
{"category": "vegetables"} // Wrong
{"category": "fruit & veg"} // Correct
```

âŒ **Cooking time as string:**
```json
{"cookingTime": "30 minutes"} // Wrong
{"cookingTime": 30} // Correct
```

âŒ **Multiple emojis:**
```json
{"image": "ğŸğŸ§„"} // Wrong
{"image": "ğŸ"} // Correct
```

âŒ **Amounts in ingredient names:**
```json
{"item": "2 cups flour"} // Wrong
{"item": "Flour", "amount": "2 cups"} // Correct
```

## ğŸ”§ **Pro Tips:**

- **Be specific with amounts**: "2 tbsp" not "some"
- **Use clear ingredient names**: "Chicken breast" not "chicken"
- **Keep instructions actionable**: Start with verbs (Cook, Add, Mix)
- **Include prep in cooking time**: Total time from start to eating
- **Choose relevant emojis**: Helps with visual recognition

Your Family Meal Planner will automatically handle the rest! ğŸš€
